
[1]deepen

   DEEPEN, v.t.

   1. To make deep or deeper; to sink lower; as, to deepen the channel of
   a river or harbor; to deepen a well.

   2. To make dark or darker; to make more thick or gloomy; as, to deepen
   the shades of night; to deepen gloom.

   3. To give a darker hue, or a stronger color; as, to deepen a color; to
   deepen a red, blue or crimson color.

   4. To make more poignant or distressing; as, to deepen grief or sorrow.

   5. To make more frightful; as, to deepen the horrors of the scene.

   6. To make more sad or gloomy; as, to deepen the murmurs of the flood.

   7. To make more grave; as, to deepen the tones of an organ.

    DEEPEN, v.i. To become more deep; as, the water deepens at every cast
                                of the lead.
